name: integer_u32_binary32_first_lost_integer
description: |
  This is 2^24 + 1, the first positive integer that does not survive conversion
  to binary32 and back. Round-to-nearest maps it to 2^24, exposing silent
  precision loss in graphics, machine-learning, database, and FFI paths.
format: hex
decode-as: u32-le
tags:
  - "integer"
  - "unsigned-integer"
  - "u32"
  - "binary32"
  - "float-roundtrip"
  - "unsafe-integer"
  - "precision-loss"
  - "boundary"
---
01 00 00 01   # 16777217 (2^24 + 1)
